      • formatDateRangeForTrieDateIndex

        String formatDateRangeForTrieDateIndex(Date beginDate,
                                     Date endDate)
        Format a date range query argument for Solr "date as trie date" index field. For example, the range 1/14/2011-1/15/2012 would return [2011-01-14T00:00:00Z TO 2012-01-15T23:59:59.999Z]
        Parameters:
        beginDate - beginning of range
        endDate - end of range
        Returns:
        Solr range query for the dates in question with the time component expanded to the entire beginning and end days.

      • formatDateRangeForStringIndex

        String formatDateRangeForStringIndex(Date beginDate,
                                   Date endDate)
        Format a date range query argument for Solr "date as string" index field. For example, the range 1/14/2011-1/15/2012 would return [2011-01-14 TO 2012-01-15] If the begin and end dates are the same only a single date string (no range) is returned.
        Parameters:
        beginDate - beginning of range
        endDate - end of range
        Returns:
        Solr range query for the dates in question or a single date if the days are the same

        Returns:
